# GD32 FOC Project Rules

## Code Style & Naming
- Functions: `Module_FunctionName` (e.g. `Timer1_Init`, `PWM_SetDutyCycle`)
- Macros: `UPPERCASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES`
- Types: `xxx_t` suffix
- Follow existing patterns unless refactoring

## Module Boundaries
- Each `Utilities/*` module is self-contained
- Clean API via header files
- Avoid cross-module globals

## Priority & Source of Truth
- **Primary source**: actual code (`.c/.h` files) is authoritative
- Secondary reference: documentation under `docs/`
- Rules in `dev-guidelines/rules/*` guide AI and collaboration

## Editable Scope
- ✅ `Application/Source`, `Application/Include`
- ✅ `Utilities/**`
- ✅ Docs: `docs/`, `NEXT_MISSION.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`
- ❌ Do not edit by default: `Firmware/**`, `.eide/**` (exceptions only for build/flash fixes)

## Interrupt Handling
- Keep ISRs short and deterministic
- Avoid blocking in ISRs; if unavoidable, ensure it cannot affect real-time behavior
- Prefer ISR forwarding to module handler functions for complex logic

## Timing & Scheduling
- Use 1kHz/100Hz/10Hz/1Hz task slots in `timer1_algorithm.c`
- Use DWT timing for execution measurement
- Initialize timers via parameterized APIs (Timer1/Timer2/PWM)

## Execution Time & 1kHz Budget
- Ensure any 1kHz task completes well under 1ms
- Use `Timer1_EnableDWT()` / `Timer1_GetExecutionTime()` to validate
- Avoid blocking delays (`delay_1ms()`) in initialization/calibration paths unless necessary
- If blocking delays are used, document execution time impact and ensure no interference with real-time tasks

## Safety
- Always include `<stddef.h>` when using `NULL`
- Do not change clocks or memory mapping without mission-level approval
- Preserve existing hardware configuration unless change is explicitly required

## Build & Flash
- Primary toolchain: Keil μVision 5 + ARM Compiler 5 (AC5)
- Development: VS Code + EIDE extension for compilation
- Flash/debug: ST-LINK (manual operation by user, AI does not perform flashing or debugging)
- Treat warnings as potential issues and resolve them

## Iteration & Documentation Contract
- Only consider a change a new iteration when user explicitly requests "进行下一次迭代"
- After each iteration, update:
  - `CHANGELOG.md` (version history)
  - `NEXT_MISSION.md` (next iteration goals)
  - `docs/` (architecture/guide updates)
  - Rules (if workflow or architecture changed)
